---
import ServiceLayout from '../../../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import RelatedServices from '../../../../components/RelatedServices.astro';

const pageData = {
  title: "Divorce Certificate Translation in Dubai – MOJ Certified | OnlineTranslation.ae",
  description: "Divorce certificate translation in Dubai accepted by UAE courts, GDRFA, and civil status authorities. MOJ-certified translations for remarriage, visa updates, and legal proceedings.",
  keywords: "divorce certificate translation dubai, divorce decree translation UAE, MOJ certified divorce certificate, remarriage UAE, divorce papers translation",
  heroTitle: "Divorce Certificate Translation in Dubai",
  heroSubtitle: "MOJ Certified for UAE Government Use",
  heroIntro: "Divorce documentation in the UAE requires careful handling. Whether you need to update your civil status, apply for remarriage, or resolve custody matters, your divorce certificate translation must meet specific court and government requirements. We review every document before translation to ensure it has the proper format and attestation for your intended use.",
  snapshot: [
    { icon: "clock", bold: "Digital drafts", text: "typically within 60 minutes" },
    { icon: "mobile-alt", bold: "WhatsApp-based workflow", text: "for easy communication" },
    { icon: "check-circle", bold: "Accepted by Dubai Courts", text: "for legal proceedings" },
    { icon: "stamp", bold: "MOJ legal stamp", text: "with QR verification" }
  ],
  breadcrumbs: [
    { name: "Home", url: "/" },
    { name: "Personal Documents", url: "/personal/" },
    { name: "Vital Records", url: "/personal/vital-records/" },
    { name: "Divorce Certificate Translation", url: "/personal/vital-records/divorce/" }
  ],
  
  trustStrip: [
    "MOJ-licensed partner",
    "Court-ready in Dubai & UAE",
    "WhatsApp concierge support"
  ],
  
  processSteps: [
    {
      title: "Send your divorce documents",
      text: "Include the divorce decree, final judgment, or certificate. Include all pages and any court stamps or seals."
    },
    {
      title: "We prepare your translation",
      text: "MOJ-licensed legal translator creates a court-ready draft with accurate legal terminology."
    },
    {
      title: "Pickup or delivery",
      text: "Collect in Dubai or arrange courier to your address. Digital PDF sent immediately upon completion."
    }
  ],
  
  benefitCards: [
    {
      icon: "court",
      title: "Court-ready translations",
      text: "Prepared with UAE court requirements in mind, including proper legal terminology and formatting."
    },
    {
      icon: "shield",
      title: "Confidential handling",
      text: "Your documents are handled with discretion. We understand the sensitive nature of divorce paperwork."
    },
    {
      icon: "document",
      title: "Complete document review",
      text: "We check that all pages, amendments, and court orders are included before translation."
    }
  ],
  
  accordionSections: [
    {
      title: "Where you will use your divorce certificate translation",
      id: "use-cases",
      items: [
        {
          heading: "Civil status updates",
          body: "<p>UAE authorities require certified translations when updating your marital status in government records. This includes Emirates ID updates, passport notations, and civil registry amendments.</p><p>The translation must accurately reflect the divorce date, parties involved, and any conditions specified in the decree.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Remarriage applications",
          body: "<p>If you are planning to remarry in the UAE or need to register a new <a href='/personal/vital-records/marriage/'>marriage</a>, you will need to provide proof of your previous divorce. Courts require MOJ-certified translations of foreign divorce decrees.</p><p>Some jurisdictions also require a waiting period before remarriage, which we can help you understand.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Visa and immigration updates",
          body: "<p>GDRFA may require divorce certificate translations when updating family visa arrangements, changing sponsorship, or applying for new residence permits as a single person.</p><p>For <a href='/services/golden-visa-translation/'>Golden Visa applicants</a>, marital status documentation is part of the application package.</p>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      title: "Special cases and requirements",
      id: "special-cases",
      items: [
        {
          heading: "Divorce granted in the UAE",
          body: "<p>If your divorce was processed through UAE courts, you likely have Arabic documentation already. However, you may still need certified translations for use with embassies, foreign governments, or English-language proceedings.</p><p>See our <a href='/services/legal-translation/'>legal translation services</a> for court-related documents.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Foreign divorce decrees",
          body: "<p>Divorce decrees from other countries typically need <a href='/services/attestation/'>attestation</a> before they can be used in the UAE. The attestation chain usually includes: issuing court or authority, home country Ministry of Foreign Affairs, UAE Embassy, and UAE MOFA.</p><p>We verify attestation status during our pre-validation review.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Multiple divorce documents",
          body: "<p>Some divorces involve multiple documents: the initial filing, interim orders, final decree, and possibly amendments. We can translate the complete set to ensure you have everything needed for UAE authorities.</p><p>Let us know your intended use so we can advise which documents are essential.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Custody and financial provisions",
          body: "<p>If your divorce decree includes custody arrangements or financial provisions that you need to enforce or reference in the UAE, these sections require particularly careful translation.</p><p>Related documents may include <a href='/personal/vital-records/birth/'>birth certificates</a> for children named in custody arrangements.</p>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      title: "Related family documents",
      id: "related",
      items: [
        {
          heading: "Birth certificates",
          body: "<p>Child custody matters often require <a href='/personal/vital-records/birth/'>birth certificate translation</a> alongside divorce documentation.</p>"
        },
        {
          heading: "Death certificates",
          body: "<p>For inheritance matters following divorce, <a href='/personal/vital-records/death/'>death certificate translation</a> may also be required.</p>"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  
  faqs: [
    {
      question: "Is this divorce certificate translation accepted for remarriage in the UAE?",
      answer: "Yes. Our MOJ-certified divorce certificate translations are accepted by UAE courts and civil authorities for remarriage applications. The translation includes all elements required by UAE law, including the official stamp and translator license details."
    },
    {
      question: "What documents do I need to provide for divorce translation?",
      answer: "At minimum, you need the final divorce decree or certificate. Depending on your situation, you may also need to provide interim orders, custody agreements, or financial settlement documents. Send us what you have, and we will advise on what is needed for your specific purpose."
    },
    {
      question: "Does my foreign divorce need to be attested before translation?",
      answer: "For most official UAE uses, yes. Foreign divorce decrees typically need attestation through your home country authorities, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, UAE Embassy, and UAE MOFA. We check this during our free pre-validation review before you pay for translation."
    },
    {
      question: "How long does divorce certificate translation take?",
      answer: "Standard service delivers within 24 hours. Express service completes in 6 hours with priority handling. VIP Concierge provides 1-hour drafts with immediate agent assignment. Complex multi-document divorces may require additional time, which we will confirm upfront."
    },
    {
      question: "Is my divorce information kept confidential?",
      answer: "Yes. We understand the sensitive nature of divorce documentation. Your documents are handled with discretion, stored securely, and only accessed by the assigned translator and quality reviewer. We do not share client information with third parties."
    }
  ],
  serviceType: "Divorce Certificate Translation"
};
---

<ServiceLayout {...pageData}>
  
  <!-- What You Receive Section -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What You Receive</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">Every divorce certificate translation includes these deliverables:</p>
      
      <div class="deliverables-grid">
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-icon"><i class="fas fa-file-pdf"></i></div>
          <h3>Digital PDF Copy</h3>
          <p>Sent via WhatsApp and email within your chosen timeframe. Suitable for initial submissions.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-icon"><i class="fas fa-stamp"></i></div>
          <h3>MOJ-Stamped Original</h3>
          <p>Physical copy with the official Ministry of Justice stamp, QR verification code, and translator license details.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-icon"><i class="fas fa-copy"></i></div>
          <h3>Certified Copies</h3>
          <p>Additional stamped copies available on request for different court or government submissions.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-icon"><i class="fas fa-truck"></i></div>
          <h3>Courier Delivery</h3>
          <p>Free delivery across Dubai. Next-day delivery to Abu Dhabi, Sharjah, and other Emirates.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing Section -->
  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Service Levels and Pricing</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">Choose the service level that matches your timeline. All options include the same quality translation and MOJ certification.</p>

      <div class="pricing-grid">
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <h3>Standard</h3>
          <div class="pricing-price">AED 150</div>
          <p class="pricing-time">24-hour delivery</p>
          <ul class="pricing-features">
            <li>MOJ-certified translation</li>
            <li>Digital PDF + physical copy</li>
            <li>Free Dubai delivery</li>
            <li>WhatsApp updates</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="pricing-card pricing-card--featured">
          <h3>Express</h3>
          <div class="pricing-price">AED 250</div>
          <p class="pricing-time">6-hour delivery</p>
          <ul class="pricing-features">
            <li>Everything in Standard</li>
            <li>Priority queue</li>
            <li>Dedicated coordinator</li>
            <li>Same-day physical delivery</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="pricing-card">
          <h3>VIP Concierge</h3>
          <div class="pricing-price">AED 450</div>
          <p class="pricing-time">1-hour draft</p>
          <ul class="pricing-features">
            <li>Everything in Express</li>
            <li>Immediate agent assignment</li>
            <li>Direct phone line</li>
            <li>Document collection service</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <RelatedServices pageKey="divorceCertificate" showFamily={true} showNextSteps={true} />
    </div>
  </section>

</ServiceLayout>

<style>
  .section-intro {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: 700px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  
  .deliverables-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .deliverable-card {
    background: #f8f9fa;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .deliverable-icon {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: var(--primary-color);
    color: #ffffff;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  
  .deliverable-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }
  
  .deliverable-card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  
  .pricing-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .pricing-card {
    background: #ffffff;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .pricing-card--featured {
    border-color: var(--accent-color);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(255, 22, 84, 0.15);
  }
  
  .pricing-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }
  
  .pricing-price {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--primary-color);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  
  .pricing-time {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .pricing-features {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: left;
  }
  
  .pricing-features li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
  }
  
  .pricing-features li::before {
    content: '✓';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent-color);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
</style>
